   <titleInfo supplied="yes">
      <title>Extracts from a letter, 1817 Mar. 2, Washington City to John C. Calhoun, Sec[retar]y of War / Rev[erend] Samuel Worcester</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Copied extract of a letter wherein Reverend Samuel Worcester, Corresponding Secretary of the American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions and missionary to the Cherokees, writes to John C. Calhoun, Secretary of War, to inform him, with regard to Indian civilization and culture, that views and dispositions of the President are in full accordance with those of the Board. The Board in which Samuel Worcester is associated deals mainly with Cherokees, Chickasaws, Choctaws, and Creeks, March 2, 1817.</abstract>
